    "caption": "The whale that sings long songs and blows bubble fishing nets.",
    "shortDescription": "Humpback whales are famous for two things: their haunting, complex songs that can last for hours, and a genius trick called bubble-net feeding — where a group of them swims in a spiral blowing bubbles to trap fish in a shimmering tube, then lunges up through the middle with a huge open mouth. Fun fact: Male humpbacks sing the same song as all the other males in their ocean — and the song slowly changes over time as whales pick up new phrases."
